# gpu-audio-lab

Research mono-repo for GPU-accelerated audio ML experiments and CUDA quantum work.

## Environment

- Python 3.11.8, venv at `.venv/`
- PyTorch 2.6+ with CUDA 12.4 (RTX 2070 Super, 8 GB VRAM)
- torchaudio, librosa, matplotlib, numpy, soundfile
- Jupyter kernel registered as `gpu-audio-lab`
- GitHub: `jeremybboy/gpu-audio-lab`

## Repo layout

```
experiments/         — one numbered folder per experiment (01-cpu-vs-gpu, 02-…)
shared/              — reusable scripts and utilities across experiments
requirements.txt     — single shared dependency list
```

## Workflow

- Each experiment lives in its own `experiments/NN-name/` folder.
- Prefer Jupyter notebooks for interactive work — pre-execute with nbconvert when sharing.
- CPU vs GPU comparisons should always include warmup runs and `torch.cuda.synchronize()`.

